1) EXPERIMENTS
  - provides a general overview of each experiment, mainly in terms of the experiment type,  microscopy setup, control strain, tested metal etc.
  - primary key: date_label
  - foreign key: wild_type_control_id: references table WILD_TYPES
                 experiment_type_id: references table EXPERIMENT_TYPES
  - columns: date_label(PK): 6-digit code corresponding to the date of experiment in format YYYYMMDD
             collection: collection from which the strains were taken (e.g., TS. thermosensitive-mutants colllection), mostly for internal labelling
             tested_metal: describes metal tested in particular experiment, mostly As (arsenic)
             data_quality: data-quality label, 'Good'/'Bad', for publication purposes only 'Good' data considered, bad data mostly due to low/extremely high cell count
             microscopy_interval_min: scanning interval of the HC microscope, ergo how often was any given field of view scanned (in minutes)
             microscopy_initial_delay: time period between exposure to metal and start of the actual microscopy, should be considered when calculating timepoints (in minutes)
             microscopy_duration_hours: duration of the entire experiment (in hours)
             number_of_fov: number of scanned fields of view
             wild_type_control_id (FK): ID of a wt/control strain used in a particular experiment
             experiment_type_id (FK): ID of a type of the particular experiment
             note: arbitrary note (for further specifications, if needed)

2)EXPERIMENT_TYPES
  - list of categories and subcategories of experiments
  - primary key: experiment_type_id
  - columns: experiment_type: describes the basic experiment type 
                              'TS collection screen': large-scale screen of the TS collection, 'SGA collection screen': large-scale screen of the SGA collection, 'WT characterisation': basic mechanisms study on the WT strain, 'Inhibitor': testing of various inhibitors
             experiment_subtype: describes the experiment subtype
                                 'first round' and 'follow-up' for the screenings, 'basic' and 'pretreatment' for the WT characterisation
             experiment_type_id (PK): unique ID for each combination type-subtype

3) WILD_TYPES
  - list of used wt/control strains
  - primary key: wild_type_control_id
  - columns: wild_type_control_id (PK): unique ID of each wt/control strain
             genotype: full genotype of the particular strain
             arbitrary_label: internal label (e.g., #260) or deletion mutation (e.g., erg6)

4) INHIBITORS
  - list (+ descriptions) of inhibitors used in the experiments of the 'Inhibitor' type
  - primary key: inhibitor_id
  - index: inhibitor_abbreviation (referenced in STRAINS_AND_CONDITIONS_INHIBITOR table)
  - columns: inhibitor_id (PK): unique ID for each inhibitor
             inhibitor_name: full name of each inhibitor
             inhibitor_abbreviation: short label for each inhibitor
             effect_description: description of the supposed effect on yeast cells (or cells in general)

5) EXPERIMENT_INHIBITOR
  - junction table between experiments and inhibitors (to accomodate the many-to-many relationship, in some experiments multiple inhibitors were used)
  - primary key (composite): date_label-inhibitor_id
  - foreign key: date_label: references table EXPERIMENTS
                 inhibitor_id: references table INHIBITORS
  - columns: date_label (PK): label of the particular experiment
             inhibitor_id (PK): ID of inhibitor used in the particular experiment

6) STRAINS_AND_CONDITIONS_MAIN
  - detailed description of experimental conditions in a specific experiment/plate (specified by the field 'date_label') - well (specified by a field 'experimental_well_label')
  - primary key (composite): date_label-collection_plate_label-experimental_well_label
  - foreign key: date_label references table EXPERIMENTS
                 mutated_gene_systematic_name: references table SGD_DESCRIPTIONS  
  - index: date_label-experimental_well_label (referenced by tables STRAINS_AND_CONDITIONS_INHIBITOR, SRAINS_AND:CONDITIONS_PRETREATMENT AND THE EXPERIMENTAL_DATA_SBW-TABLES)
  - columns: date_label (PK): 6-digit code corresponding to the date of experiment in format YYYYMMDD
             collection_plate_label (PK): label of the plate from TS collection (only applicable to TS screening, otherwise '-')
             experimental_well_label (PK): label of the specific well in the imaging plate (does not always correspond to the well in collection plate- collection plates are 96-well, imaging plates are 384-well)
             corresponding_collection_well_label: label of the well in the 'collection_plate_label' (only applicable to TS screening, otherwise '-' or '')
             mutated_gene_systematic_name: systematic name of the mutated gene ('-' if WT)
             mutated_gene_standard_name: standard name of the mutated gene ('-' if WT)
             mutation: specific mutation ('wt control' for WT)
             biological_repeat: repeat label (1-3)
             medium: used medium (almost exclusively YNB- complete)
             metal_concentration
             metal_concentration_unit

7) STRAINS_AND_CONDITIONS_INHIBITOR
  - extension of the STRAINS_AND_CONDITIONS_MAIN table, applicable for experiments of the 'Inhibitor' type
  - primary key (composite): date_label-experimental_well_label
  - foreign key: date_label-experimental_well_label (composite): references table STRAINS_AND_CONDITIONS_MAIN
                 inhibitor_abbreviation: references table INHIBITORS
  - columns: date_label (PK, FK): 6-digit code corresponding to the date of experiment in format YYYYMMDD
             experimental_well_label (PK, FK): label of the specific well in the imaging plate 
             inhibitor_abbreviation (FK): abb. of used inhibitor
             inhibitor_concentration: final concentration of the used inhibitor
             inhibitor_concentration_unit
             inhibitor_solvent: solvent of the used inhibitor (e.g., DMSO)
             inhibitor_solvent_concentration: final concentration of the solvent (after adding the inhibitor into media)
             inhibitor_solvent_concentration_unit: usually %

8) STRAINS_AND_CONDITIONS_PRETREATMENT
  - extension of the STRAINS_AND_CONDITIONS_MAIN table, applicable for experiments of the 'WT characterisation' type - 'pretreatment' subtype
  - primary key (composite): date_label-experimental_well_label
  - foreign key: date_label-experimental_well_label (composite): references table STRAINS_AND_CONDITIONS_MAIN
  - columns: date_label (PK, FK): 6-digit code corresponding to the date of experiment in format YYYYMMDD
             experimental_well_label (PK, FK): label of the specific well in the imaging plate
             pretreatment: conditions of pretreatment (As- for As-exposed cells (media + As), control- for control cells (media))
             pretreatment_metal_concentration
             pretreatment_metal_concentration_unit
             pretreatment_duration_min
